.TH "imr_check_params" 9 "imr_check_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
imr_check_params \- check passed address range IMR alignment and non-zero size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" imr_check_params
.BI "(phys_addr_t base "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
base address of intended IMR.
.IP "size" 12
size of intended IMR.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on valid range -EINVAL on unaligned base/size.
